:: Case 3 introduction 

A 50-year-old female patient enters the examination room in the emergency department. She complains of coughing, fatigue and dyspnea when walking to her place of work, which is located around 2km from her house. This has been happening for a few months and getting gradually worse. A doctor in the past has told her that she has high blood pressure. 

/% Hint left heart failure more. %/
She has also been coughing consistently 2-3 days per week at night, which has bothered her sleep. 
Vitals: BP 140/90mmHg, HR 92 bpm, T: 37.7 degrees Celcius, SpO2 = 94% on room air. 
